<div id="review_2915570002" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2915570002" />
    <a title="Green Pastures" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100595436-green-pastures"><img alt="Green Pastures" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1564405048p2/100595436.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2915570002?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Green Pastures" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Green Pastures" href="/user/show/100595436-green-pastures">Green Pastures</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2915570002" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer570755625189980211">This book is like holding hands with the author, and allowing her to accompany you on your own difficult journey (whatever stage that may be at). At times a very emotive read, making it a little difficult, it&apos;s worth persevering with. Lavender brings to the forefront the message that there can be a great strength found from loss, sadness and adversity. Grief is a very personal thing, and we all have our own coping mechanisms. The author doesn&apos;t try to over-shadow this, nor does it come across as</span>
  <span id="freeText570755625189980211" style="display:none">This book is like holding hands with the author, and allowing her to accompany you on your own difficult journey (whatever stage that may be at). At times a very emotive read, making it a little difficult, it's worth persevering with. Lavender brings to the forefront the message that there can be a great strength found from loss, sadness and adversity. Grief is a very personal thing, and we all have our own coping mechanisms. The author doesn't try to over-shadow this, nor does it come across as dictating or patronising. Lavender shares her inspiration on how to cope, how to move forward, and offers the reader a sense of empathy and thus, comfort. Add in some art-work which incorporates nature, angels and butterflies, and this collection becomes a thing of beauty. I will be buying this for a dear friend who is in need of a little strength.</span>
  <a data-text-id="570755625189980211" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


