<div id="review_2492350165" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2492350165" />
    <a title="Bookish Picks" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70742672-bookish-picks"><img alt="Bookish Picks" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1534163745p2/70742672.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2492350165?book_show_action=true">Aug 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bookish Picks" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bookish Picks" href="/user/show/70742672-bookish-picks">Bookish Picks</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2492350165" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer543761985981411973">This heartfelt collection of observations and beliefs by Diamante Lavendar is a collection of her artwork and creative writing. She shares photography, illustration and prose/poetry that explore her inner feelings and emotions. Her daughter died at age 18 and Diamante’s wish is to extend the strength that she has found confronting her grief and pain, through the sharing of her words and images. She simply offers intimate bite-sized thoughts for readers to gain inspiration and hope from, allowing</span>
  <span id="freeText543761985981411973" style="display:none">This heartfelt collection of observations and beliefs by Diamante Lavendar is a collection of her artwork and creative writing. She shares photography, illustration and prose/poetry that explore her inner feelings and emotions. Her daughter died at age 18 and Diamante’s wish is to extend the strength that she has found confronting her grief and pain, through the sharing of her words and images. She simply offers intimate bite-sized thoughts for readers to gain inspiration and hope from, allowing us to take in one at a time, dip in and out or take our time and indulge in more. I particularly liked Diamante’s black and white photographs; I found them intriguing and equally as thought-provoking as her writing. I recommended Finding Hope in the Darkness of Grief as a spiritual pick-me-up for anyone seeking comfort. </span>
  <a data-text-id="543761985981411973" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


