        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2983036254" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13992471982166462556">Empowering poetic journal reaching out to anyone who loves reading soothing, inspiring verse. Pages are uniquely designed to reflect not only the essence of poetry but the brave style of hand drawn art both black and white and color.<br/><br/>I’m moved by the author’s approach to her book and hope it succeeds. My favorite poem is called “Take Time To Know Me” about children&apos;s innocence and teaching painting with a beautiful message to not grow up… too much. The paintings included in the book are a remarka</span>
  <span id="freeText13992471982166462556" style="display:none">Empowering poetic journal reaching out to anyone who loves reading soothing, inspiring verse. Pages are uniquely designed to reflect not only the essence of poetry but the brave style of hand drawn art both black and white and color.<br /><br />I’m moved by the author’s approach to her book and hope it succeeds. My favorite poem is called “Take Time To Know Me” about children's innocence and teaching painting with a beautiful message to not grow up… too much. The paintings included in the book are a remarkable addition to now, my favorite book. With the passion of brushstrokes black, purple and white I see myself in the shadows of the poetry as if I am experiencing the imagery scenes myself in real time, as the reader.<br />Empathetic poetry writing keen to loss, hardships and the energies to make yourself feel whole again. This book is not read in grieving times but anyone who sees themselves as needing more strength, bravery, and perseverance.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13992471982166462556" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
