    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2774809112" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2774809112" />
    <a title="The Wise Old Tree" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/95641632-the-wise-old-tree"><img alt="The Wise Old Tree" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1554389943p2/95641632.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2774809112?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="The Wise Old Tree" class="user" itemprop="url" name="The Wise Old Tree" href="/user/show/95641632-the-wise-old-tree">The Wise Old Tree</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2774809112" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17589187084651344898">This is a beautiful and deeply personal piece by Diamante Lavendar. “Every hardship has a reason, and every deprivation a purpose, if you look through eyes of insight.” This line is so reflective of Lavender’s ability to allow light and joy and purpose to exist within pain and loss. That is what was so touching about this book for me. There are so many gorgeous lines in this book that offer the reader hope, faith, and a feeling of unity and understanding. It is clear that the author may have exp</span>
  <span id="freeText17589187084651344898" style="display:none">This is a beautiful and deeply personal piece by Diamante Lavendar. “Every hardship has a reason, and every deprivation a purpose, if you look through eyes of insight.” This line is so reflective of Lavender’s ability to allow light and joy and purpose to exist within pain and loss. That is what was so touching about this book for me. There are so many gorgeous lines in this book that offer the reader hope, faith, and a feeling of unity and understanding. It is clear that the author may have experienced a dark time before understanding that pain does not have to be suffered alone. The artwork in juxtaposition with the poetry plays very nicely together. Some of the pieces reflect a deep sadness but also give a sense of light and hope. It is clear that this book was full the ideas, reflections, thoughts, and perspectives that Diamante uses to navigate grief. This book is both beautiful and completely useful and relevant to so many people. If you are experiencing a loss and are seeking some light in the darkness and compassion from someone who has experiences deep personal loss, this is the book for you. This is a fantastic contribution to literature on this subject and I can see this touching many people and helping them find a way through the darkness of loss and grief.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17589187084651344898" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


